title: Cannot Install [test] Dependencies
body:
After successfully installing base Ludwig 0.3 packages, I cannot install test dependencies using the following:

`pip install ludwig[test]`

After lengthy reporting of already satisfied requirements, the process fails as shown in the terminal output below, reporting that it cannot build wheels for horovod or sci-diet image and mentioning PEP 517.

I realize the terminal output is long and dense, but I wonder if anyone has experienced a similar issue. Also, is there additional information on the test dependencies and for what use cases they are applied? I may not even require them.

I am running macOS Catalina (10.15.7) with Python 3.8.5 in a Conda environment.

Thanks very much.

David Wilt

P.S. My apologies for not being able to apply code formatting to the terminal output. Any suggestions?
